At a party, Ted's age is 15 years less than twice Sally's age. The sum of their ages is 54. How old is Ted? ||| Let Ted's age be $t$ and Sally's age be $s$. The equations we set up are:\ 
\begin{align*}
 t &= s - 15 \\ 
 t + s &= 54 \\ 
\end{align*} 
From the second equation, we can express $s$ as $s = 54 - t$. Substituting this into the first equation gives $t = (54 - t) - 15$. Solving this leads us to $2t = 54 - 15$, and thus $t = 19.5$. Therefore, Ted's age is \boxed{19.5}.

At a party, Ted's age is 15 years less than twice Sally's age. The sum of their ages is 54. How old is Ted? ||| Let Ted's age be $t$ and Sally's age be $s$. We can formulate the equations as:\ 
\begin{align*}
 t &= 2s + 15 \\ 
 t + s &= 54 \\ 
\end{align*} 
From the second equation, we get $s = 54 - t$. Substituting back gives $t = 2(54 - t) + 15$. Solving for $t$ results in $t = 108 - 2t + 15$, thus $3t = 123$, which gives $t = 41$. Hence, Ted is \boxed{41} years old.

