Simplify $(2x - 5)(x + 7) - (x + 5)(2x - 1)$. ||| We can expand the first product: 
\begin{align*}
(2x-5)(x+7) &= 2x\cdot x + 2x\cdot 7 - 5\cdot x - 5\cdot 7 \\
&= 2x^2 + 14x - 5x - 35 \\
&= 2x^2 + 9x - 35.
\end{align*}

For the second product,
\begin{align*}
(x+5)(2x-1) &= x\cdot 2x + x\cdot (-1) + 5\cdot 2x + 5\cdot (-1) \\
&= 2x^2 - x + 10x - 5 \\
&= 2x^2 + 9x - 5.
\end{align*}

So we are left with \begin{align*}
(2x-5)(x+7) - (x+5)(2x-1) &= 2x^2 + 9x - 35 - (2x^2 + 9x + 5) \\
&= 2x^2 + 9x - 35 - 2x^2 - 9x - 5 \\
&= -40.
\end{align*}
\boxed{-40}

