a+b+c&=24\\
a+c&=2b\\
a+b&=c\end{align*} Rearranging the second equation, we can find $b$: \begin{align*}
a+c&=2b \Rightarrow b=\frac{a+c}{2}\end{align*} Now let's substitute this expression for $b$ into Equation (1): \begin{align*}
a+\frac{a+c}{2}+c&=24\Rightarrow 2a+a+c+2c=48 \Rightarrow 3a+3c=48\Rightarrow a+c=16\end{align*} Using Equation (2) rearranged, we take $c=2b-a$ and substitute to find that \begin{align*}a+\frac{2b-a}{2}&=b \Rightarrow 2a+2b-a=2b \Rightarrow a=0\end{align*} Thus, the puppy weighs \boxed{0} pounds.

