Now analyzing it from the third row, we have 24 + z + w = 66. Replacing w with 23 again gives us 24 + z + 23 = 66, leading us to z = 19.  
Moving forward, from the top row: 25 + 18 + v = 66  
v must therefore be 23. Then checking other values we have: x = 20, y=23.  To finalize: y + z = 23 + 19 = \boxed{42}.

